{{Infobox company |name = Answer Underground |logo = |type = Private |traded_as = |industry = [[Mobile computing|Mobile]], [[Social networking|Social]], elearning, [[online tutoring]] |foundation = [[San Francisco, California|San Francisco]], [[California]], United States ({{Start date|2012}}) |founder = [[Sallie Severns]], CEO |location_city = [[San Francisco, California]] |location_country = U.S. |area_served = U.S. |key_people = |products = {{unbulleted list|Answer Underground}} |revenue = |operating_income = |net_income = |assets = |equity = |num_employees = |subsid = |homepage = {{URL|http://www.answerunderground.com/ }} }}
'''Answer Underground''' was a social education company based in [[San Francisco]], California. It developed an app for teachers and students to find information via group Q&A.
== History == Answer Underground was founded in 2012<ref>The EdTech Times, 15 Jan 2013, [http://edtechtimes.com/2013/01/15/qa-with-sallie-severns-ceo-of-qa-based-mobile-study-app-answer-underground Q&A with Sallie Severns, CEO of Q&A-based mobile study app Answer Underground], Retrieved 10 Sep 2013.</ref> by Sallie Severns, a former executive at information company [[Answers.com]].<ref name = "TechCrunch">[https://techcrunch.com/2012/08/12/answer-underground-aims-to-be-a-mobile-focused-quora-for-education-hits-the-ipad-this-week/ Answer Underground Aims To Be A Mobile-Focused Quora For Education, Hits The iPad This Week], retrieved 10 Sep 2013.</ref> Severns came up with the idea for a mobile collaborative elearning app after observing her son struggle to get homework help online.{{cn|date=November 2017}}
Severns created the first prototype of the Answer Underground app in 2011 and it was released to open beta in May 2012.<ref name = "SiliconAngle">[http://siliconangle.com/blog/2013/01/15/mobile-qa-app-for-students-adds-teacher-verified-answers/ Mobile Q&A App for Students Adds Teacher Verified Answers], Retrieved 10 Sep 2013.</ref> == Service == Originally, the Answer Underground app was designed for mobile devices and was optimized for [[iOS]]. Users were authenticated through [[Facebook]].<ref name = "TechCrunch" /> As of September 2013, the company had planned to release the app for the [[Android (operating system)|Android operating system]].<ref>The EdTech Times, 15 Jan 2013, [http://edtechtimes.com/2013/01/15/mobile-qa-based-study-app-answer-underground-launches-features-to-verify-contributors-answers/ Mobile Q&A-based study app Answer Underground launches features to verify contributors’ answers], Retrieved 10 Sep 2013.</ref>
The app focused on academic groups categorized by major subject areas. Members were able to post questions to academic groups. In 2013, a verification feature was added to identify experienced academics to differentiate credible responses.<ref name = "SiliconAngle" /><ref>{{cite web| url= https://thenextweb.com/apps/2013/01/15/groupsourced-educational-app-answer-underground-launches-verified-accounts-for-academics/| title=Groupsourced educational app Answer Underground launches verified accounts for academics| publisher=The Next Web| author=Alex Wilhelm| date=January 15, 2013| access-date=November 8, 2017}}</ref>
